This spontaneous report was received from a consumer or other non health professional (patient's parent) and 
concerns a 10-month-old male patient from the United States: 017436009A.
The patient's height and weight was not reported. 
The patient's medical history included cochlear implants and deaf. 
The patient was treated with paracetamol (unspecified, unspecified route, unspecified dose and frequency) initiated 
on an unspecified date for  cochlear implant pain. Concomitant medications were not reported.
On an unspecified date, the consumer reported, her son just had surgery to get his cochlear implants. So she 
bought 3 boxes to be safe if needed at late night where stores are closed. After opening the first box and nothing 
was wrapped in the box.The second one was the same way (package did not have security seal) (product 
packaging issue) so she opened the third box and it was wrapped and sealed.Consumer may have given the 
product to her son, who is too young to receive it (drug administered to patient of inappropriate age) (off label use).
Action taken with paracetamol was not reported.
The outcome was not reported for off label use, drug administered to patient of inappropriate age, package did not 
have security seal and product packaging issue. 
This report was associated with the product complaint and product complaint number was not reported.
This report was not serious.